		<div id="comment_body_64516591"><p><span class="substr"> </span><div class="quote"><p>...*and* cheaper to drive. It costs me $40 round trip to drive my big EV truck 400 miles. It costs my friend $120 to drive the exact same distance in their small SUV.</p></div><p>It really depends on where you live.  Where I'm at electricity costs $0.36/kWh ($0.18/kWh + approximately the same cost in "delivery fees").  The savings from the EV at that rate aren't all that they are cracked up to be.  1 gal of gas = 33.7 kWh of energy.  That 33.7 kWh costs me $12.13.  With an EV efficiency of 3.5 mi / kWh, that 33.7 kWh @ $12.77 will take me ~42.5 mi.</p><p>The average rate for for gas in my state is ~$4/gal. So that same $12 will buy me ~3 gal of gas.  Assuming a middle of the road sedan @</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64516591">

</div>
</div>

